-! # how to errors: 061-zsx-unclosed-tag.zo
-!
-! @cmd: `zo build 061-zsx-unclosed-tag.zo`
-!
-! #template
-!
-! Every ZSX tag is like a room. If you open a `<div>`, you must 
-! close it with a `</div>`. If you leave it open, your layout 
-! "leaks" into the rest of the file. 
-!
-! zo stops you here so your UI structure is always solid.

fun main() {
  -- Mistake: Missing the closing </div> tag.
  imu view: </> ::= <div>
    <h1>"Unfinished UI"</h1>;
}

-! ## The Diagnostic:
-!
-! The compiler finds the end of the expression (the `;`) before it finds the
-! closing tag. 
-!
-!   - For the Human:** You opened a `<div>` but forgot to shut the door.
-!   - **For the Agent:** Error [E0061]. Target: Line 15, Column 19. 
-!     Expected: `</div>`.
-!
-! ## try this.
-!
-! 1. Add `</div>` before the semicolon on line 16.
-! 2. Try using a self-closing tag for empty elements: 
-!    `<img src="logo.png" />`. Notice how this doesn't need a partner!

-- EXPECTED OUTPUT:
-- [E0061] Error: Unclosed ZSX tag
--    ┌─ 061-zsx-unclosed-tag.zo:15:19
--    │
-- 15 │   imu view: </> = <div>
--    │                   ^─── unclosed tag started here
--    │
--    = Note: Every ZSX element must be closed with either `</tag>` or a self-closing `/>`.
--    = Help: Add a closing `</div>` tag at line 16, column 1.
-- ────╯
